{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/vigramsdk\/step1gettingstarted"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step1GettingStarted"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To connect VigramSDK in this example we will use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.swift.org\/package-manager\/"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"We also recommend using this method instead of CocoaPods."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Step-1-Add-Package-Dependencies-in-your-project","level":2,"text":"Step 1. Add Package Dependencies in your project.","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a framework to your project, you need to select Add Package Dependencies in the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"File"}]},{"type":"text","text":" section of the top menu of Xcode:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"fig1.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Paste into the search bar url:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["https:\/\/github.com\/vigram-sw\/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution.git"],"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"fig2.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After entering the address, the SDK name, the current release version, and the project to which the library will be added will appear:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"fig3.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Make sure you have access to an internet connection and tha